article.description: — Aaron Cash scored 17 points as UT Arlington beat Seattle 80-75 on Saturday night.
article.headline: UT Arlington wins 80-75 over Seattle
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- — Aaron Cash scored 17 points as UT Arlington beat Seattle 80-75 on Saturday night. Cash also contributed five rebounds for the Mavericks (8-9, 3-3 Western Athletic Conference). DaJuan Gordon added 16 points while going 5 of 6 and 5 of 9 from the free-throw line, and he also had eight rebounds. Shemar Wilson shot 4 of 4 from the field and 5 for 6 from the line to finish with 13 points. John Christofilis led the Redhawks (10-7, 3-3) in scoring, finishing with 22 points and two steals. Alex Schumacher added 21 points, eight assists and two steals for Seattle. Paris Dawson also recorded nine points, four assists and three steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
